messages:
Name: Andre Gray
Nationality: Jamaica
Date of Birth: June 26, 1991
Position: Attacker
Current club: Plymouth Argyle
Championship clubs played for: Brentford, Burnley, Watford, Queens Park Rangers, Plymouth Argyle

Attacker Andre Gray plays for Plymouth Argyle and has appeared in 13 Championship matches in 2024/2025 since joining the club on 4th October 2024, being selected in the starting XI in five of these and being mostly used off the bench on eight occasions.

Gray last made an appearance in a Championship game on January 1, playing just four minutes for Plymouth Argyle versus Bristol City in a 2-2 draw. In total, the attacker has scored three Championship goals this term, making him tied as the team's top league scorer, and chipped in with one assist. He has been shown a yellow card once.
It was against Watford on November 22 when Gray last scored, netting with a brace in a 2-2 draw. His opening goal of the campaign came in the 3-3 draw against Preston North End on October 26.
Next up in the league for Plymouth Argyle is a home match against Burnley on January 22.
Last season for Al Riyadh, Gray made 26 Saudi League appearances, scored seven goals and provided two assists.
Gray moved to Plymouth Argyle in October 2024 from Al Riyadh, for whom he made 26 league appearances in total, scoring seven goals and providing two assists.
